member.name: CRYPT_OID_FUNC_ENTRY
member.summary: The CRYPT_OID_FUNC_ENTRY structure contains an object identifier (OID) and a pointer to its related function. It is used with.

member.name: CRYPT_OID_FUNC_ENTRY.pszOID
member.summary: If the high-order word of the OID is nonzero, pszOID is a pointer to either an OID string, such as "2.5.29.1" or an ASCII string, such as "file". If the high-order word of the OID is zero, the low-order word specifies the numeric identifier to be used as the object identifier.

member.name: CRYPT_OID_FUNC_ENTRY.pvFuncAddr
member.summary: The starting address of the function that the OID identifies.
